programme.title: Supercars
programme.desc: The Tushek TS600, a super sports car built in Austria, was limited to 33 units, extremely light and had a power/weight ratio that is on the level of GT3 racing cars. But the best thing about this racer made of titanium, carbon and aluminum was that it was street-legal. The Bentley Continental GT3-R special edition was also limited to 300 units whereas McLaren offered their 570S to all customers.

programme.title: Supercars
programme.desc: Almost every big car manufacturer has its own tuning company where regular models are awarded an improved performance and a sportier look. But there are customers who aim for even more exclusivity. The German company Performmaster upgraded the Mercedes C63 AMG S, chip tuning from the Racechip company gave the Porsche Macan Turbo even more bite and Kellener did their take on the BMW 640i.

programme.title: Supercars
programme.desc: How do high performance super cars fare in a cold climate? Nissan's all-wheel monster GT-R had to prove its winter suitability and the new Porsche 911 with turbo engine was taken to its limits in Finnish Lapland. Also: the Mercedes-Benz S 500 plug-in hybrid.

programme.title: Porsche Cayman GT4
programme.desc: The Porsche Cayman GT4. Lighter, more powerful and faster than ever. Porsche shows what is possible with this vehicle, when fast lap times are in the focus of attention.

programme.title: Volvo XC60
programme.desc: The Swedish landscape is characterized by mountains, forests and lonely roads. Ideal for this off-roader. The Volvo XC60 scores with many safety features and a cool appearance.

programme.title: Jeep Renegade
programme.desc: Jeep has been building SUVs since 1942. The Jeep Renegade comes from a traditional home. It is the youngest representative of the family and the most successful.

programme.title: Jeep Wrangler
programme.desc: In 2018 the fourth generation of the Wrangler was introduced. I contained state-of-the-art technology, but the rugged look remained the same. The brand works hard to maintain this silhouette since the very first Jeep ever, the Willys MB.

programme.title: Toyota MegaCruiser BXD10
programme.desc: The Toyota MegaCruiser BXD10 has its origins in the Japanese army. Its shape won’t win any beauty contests or achieve the best results in the wind tunnel, but this is not really the point with an SUV like this.

programme.title: Volvo Laplander 6x6
programme.desc: More extremes are always possible. Volvo's Laplander army vehicle has 6 wheels, 3 axles and provides space for at least 12 soldiers.

programme.title: Lancia Stratos HF
programme.desc: The Lancia Stratos with Ferrari power, the rally icon of the 1970s.

programme.title: Amphicar 770
programme.desc: The amphicar 770 is a unique and rare classic. It may not be the fastest car on the street, but it's always ready for getting in the water.

programme.title: Volkswagen Polo R WRC
programme.desc: For Volkswagen, the VW Polo R WRC was a means to an end in order to be allowed to compete in the World Rally Championship. For the homologation of the rally car, Volkswagen had to build the basic car in small series.

programme.title: Dreamcars
programme.desc: The BMW X5M, Audi Q7, Mercedes GLS and Porsche Cayenne Turbo are among the strongest and fastest SUVs in the world. Sports utility vehicles made in Germany are the embodiment of technical perfection, superior performance and unique comfort.

programme.title: Dreamcars
programme.desc: Luxury, lifestyle and exclusivity, no other cars transport these attributes better than the SUVs by Jaguar, Range Rover, Bentley, Volvo and Infinity. These stylish and excellently equipped SUVs embody a spirit of adventure and a zest for life.

programme.title: Dreamcars
programme.desc: US SUVs and pickup trucks like the Cadillac Escalade, Chevrolet Tahoe, Ford Raptor or Dodge Ram are large, powerful and luxurious and exude the feeling of unlimited possibilities and adventure.

programme.title: Toyota MegaCruiser BXD10
programme.desc: The Toyota MegaCruiser BXD10 has its origins in the Japanese army. Its shape won’t win any beauty contests or achieve the best results in the wind tunnel, but this is not really the point with an SUV like this.

programme.title: Ford GT40
programme.desc: With their V8 cars, Ford showed that they were able to build race winners. The Ford GT40 was a prime example for that, especially in Le Mans.

programme.title: Aston Martin Rapide S
programme.desc: Aston Martin is breaking new ground with the sport sedan – the „Rapide S“. Ever since the official car of James Bond became the Aston Martin, this brand has achieved cult status. Desirable, timelessly elegant, 2-door sports coupes are the DNA. But even the venerable British brand does not escape evolution - because with the Rapide S, Aston Martin goes new ways.

programme.title: Supercars
programme.desc: The Tesla Model S was the world's first premium sedan that was developed from scratch as an electric car. Tesla showed the world that electromobility can be sexy and, even more importantly, that it works. We took a closer look at the 700 hp Model S P85D with two electric engines and examined Tesla's supercharging technology.

programme.title: Supercars
programme.desc: The Mercedes‘ S-Class Coupe is a real masterpiece. The significantly sportier two-door version of the S-Class doesn’t just look really good, it could also succeed in attracting Bentley or even Rolls Royce customers. We explored what the S 63 AMG Coupe has to offer in comparison to the Bentley Continental and the Rolls Royce Wraith.

programme.title: Supercars
programme.desc: With the Ghibli, the Italian sports car manufacturer Maserati advanced into a more affordable market segment in order to attract a new clientele. But the competition, namely the BMW 5 series, Mercedes-Benz' E-Class, the Audi A6 or Jaguar's XF model, is strong. In addition: taking the Maserati GranCabrio MC on a cruise through the Alps.

programme.title: Supercars
programme.desc: The Aston Martin V12 Vantage S Roadster with its 6-litre V12 engine is probably the most amazing export from the UK. It's the British brand's highest-powered convertible of all time. Does it live up to the expectations? In addition: a mountain cruise from dawn to dusk with the Corvette C7 Convertible.

programme.title: Supercars
programme.desc: The Porsche Cayman GT4 combined the best elements that Porsche could offer: the V6 Boxer engine from the 911 Carrera S, the chassis, brake system and aerodynamics from the GT3, and a six-gear transmission. In addition: the Audi R8 V10 plus, an even stronger, lighter and faster version of the original model.

programme.title: Rolls-Royce Dawn Convertible
programme.desc: Almost silently, it glides through the night. In front of the driver 12 smoothly-running cylinders are at work, with a power reserve that seems inexhaustible. The Rolls Royce Dawn is a convertible for connoisseurs.

programme.title: Rolls-Royce Wraith
programme.desc: The Rolls Royce Wraith is different. It gives the traditional British brand a whole new dynamic.

programme.title: Trackmasters
programme.desc: In this episode we invite you to witness the progress of driver Uwe Nittle as he got ready for qualifying at the Truck Grand Prix.

programme.title: Trackmasters
programme.desc: The RCN Challenge is the ultimate BMW driving experience. We also paid a visit to the Devils Diner, the track's indoor meeting place for drivers.

programme.title: Trackmasters
programme.desc: After the 24-hour race was over we left the Nürburgring and moved to Büren, Germany, where the Raeder Motorsport company is based. They are famous for front-wheel drives with a great performance that put a lot of horsepower to the track.

programme.title: Trackmasters
programme.desc: The roaring sounds of engines and exhausts usually dominate the Nürburgring, but we focused on something a bit quieter this time. How about taking part in a 15 mile bike ride around the ring, or perhaps a 16 mile run?

programme.title: Artega GT
programme.desc: From 2006 to 2012 the German company Artega produced their GT sports car model. Thanks to the know-how of a former Porsche and BMW manager the Artega GT was able to be manufactured in a small series.

programme.desc: The Swedish landscape is characterized by mountains, forests and lonely roads. Ideal for this off-roader. The Volvo XC60 scores with many safety features and a cool appearance.

programme.title: Perfect Ride
programme.desc: Smart offers its iconic city car with a convertible option. The Mini cabriolet is bigger and provides room for four people. When it comes to roadster feeling, the Mazda MX-5 is on top of the list. We took a closer look at these three open-top contenders.

programme.title: Perfect Ride
programme.desc: The Paris Motor Show features the automotive world of tomorrow. In 2016 Mercedes-Benz introduced their “Generation EQ” and Volkswagen announced to build 20 new electrified models by 2020, possibly in order to distract from the emission scandal.

programme.title: Perfect Ride
programme.desc: What would make coupe fans opt for a more traditional two-door model like the Mercedes-Benz E400 instead of its bigger brother, the CLS with four doors? Also: does the Volkswagen Arteon stand a chance against the Mercedes CLS?

programme.title: Arden AJ23
programme.desc: A Jaguar that is able to terrify the world alone with its roar. This Jaguar F-Type R tuned by Arden is a real bad boy. Already in the series production configuration, the F-Type R Coupe is a dream car that can really bite but this Jaguar which has been upgraded from Arden, now calls itself "AJ23“ and is more powerful, louder and more aggressive than any of his brothers.

programme.title: Volvo S90
programme.desc: It looks sportier than one might expect from the Swedes. The taillights frame the powerful looking rear. On the inside, the Volvo S90 impresses with the finest materials and soft nappa leather.

programme.title: Audi MTM S8 Talladega R
programme.desc: The Audi S8 Plus is by no means underpowered, but it is and remains faithful to this model series' understatement. Those who want more power can get a boost from MTM.

programme.title: Trackmasters
programme.desc: An angry bull, a few Englishmen who prepared themselves for rather unpleasant weather conditions and a young, talented race driver, these were all visitors who ventured to the infamous Green Hell of the Nürburgring.

programme.title: Trackmasters
programme.desc: A tuned-up Golf 2, a family sedan from Hanover, Germany and a very special Porsche GT2. We looked behind the scenes of the gas station by the curve on the race track where sports cars flock.

programme.title: Trackmasters
programme.desc: When the Nürburgring transforms into a winter wonderland, it may look pleasant but sure isn't too pleasant as a race track.

programme.title: Trackmasters
programme.desc: Fog, rain and snow means that a visit to the Eifel region isn't too pleasant. Nevertheless, the toughest drivers were at the track, not letting the weather get in their way.

programme.title: Jaguar XJR
programme.desc: The highlight of the XJR lies beneath the hood: all of Jaguar's top models are equipped with the 5-liter V8 compressor engine that delivers 550 HP in this sports sedan.

programme.title: Car History
programme.desc: From the very beginning of its company history, AMG has set itself the goal of being the epitome of automotive top performance, exclusivity and dynamic driving pleasure under the sign of the Mercedes star.

programme.title: Car History
programme.desc: Legendary racing successes, technological innovations and exclusive vehicles were main contributors to the Lancia brand's worldwide fame. Its history was marked by ups and downs, but Lancia is still held in high esteem.

programme.title: Car History
programme.desc: The BMW motorsport division has been a success story since its foundation, and not only on the race track. The high-performance road cars with the letter M on the rear caused worldwide enthusiasm right from the start.

programme.title: Car History
programme.desc: From tame and conservative to avant-garde, in the 1960s and 70s Ford built one classic after another, always following the proven formula of the company: simple technology, appealing shapes, affordable price.

programme.title: Car History
programme.desc: The classic car models by Volvo are sometimes square and angular, sometimes rounded and smooth. They are reliable, resilient and comfortable, with a unique style and feel. Almost every Volvo model was an instant classic.

programme.title: Audi TT RS Roadster
programme.desc: A roadster with a roaring racing engine: the Audi TT RS has the company's legendary 5-cylinder sports engine under the hood. Does this iconic engine match the fashionable packaging?

programme.title: Bentley Mulsanne EWB
programme.desc: The long version of the Bentley Mulsanne is a prime example of a chauffeured limousine. With it, the British luxury car brand has set the bar extremely high when it comes to automotive comfort.

programme.title: BMW Active Hybrid 7
programme.desc: With the Active Hybrid 7, unlike with its predecessor bearing the same model name, BMW now banks on a full hybrid, which can also be driven solely with electric power.

programme.desc: We show the highlights of the MXGP on 16 and 17 July in Loket, Czech Republic.

programme.title: FIM World Motocross Championship

programme.title: Motorcycles
programme.desc: Assistance systems on two-wheelers, such as the blind spot warning system from BMW. Also: the C 650 GT maxi-scooter with assistance system in Valencia. Is the Side View Assist a paternalism or a real help?

programme.title: Strongman Champions League
programme.desc: Welcome to Kokkola in Finland. This city will be the setting for the Lightweight World championship. Out of 24 athletes, only 16 will make it through to the final day, but who will champion each event and who is going to be eliminated?

programme.title: Strongman Champions League
programme.desc: Its the second day, and the top 16 athletes have made it through to the final round. With another 4 events to go who will get the crown of world champion?

programme.title: Strongman Champions League
programme.desc: Welcome to Ukraine and the wonderful capital city of Kyiv. Were here for the second time for the iconic truck pull World Championships! The reigning World champion Kelvin de Ruiter from Holland will defend his title.

programme.title: Strongman Champions League
programme.desc: In this episode, a final chance for our athletes to get vital world series ranking points on board to give them the best possible chance of success and an initial advantage at the finals. It's the last show before the world finals and the top 10 places are up for grabs, but who will they be?

programme.title: Strongman Champions League
programme.desc: We are in Alanya, on Turkeys south-coast for the final stop at the end of a mammoth season. Here in the sunshine, well finally crown our world champion and what a place Alanya is - you could not ask for a better setting. Aivars Smaukstellis, the reigning world champion is defending his title, and two-time world champion Dainis Zageris is also here, but with a though competition, who will win?

programme.title: Strongman Champions League
programme.desc: What a day ahead of us here in Alanya, just a handful of events to go before we find out who will be the winner of Strongman Champions League in 2021. These are the world finals, and all the big names are in the house. With just 3 events to go - who will take the crown of World Champion 2021 and be the STRONGEST?

programme.title: Strongman Champions League
programme.desc: We are back, after a short break it feels like we never even left. We’re here in Vaasa - Finland kicking off 2022 new world series. If you are watching at home, just like these people, you’re in the right place. Because this is a special edition world record breaker. The only question left today, is to see how many new world records will be set so stay tuned.

programme.title: Strongman Champions League
programme.desc: We are here in Doetinchem – Holland, for Stage 2 and 3 in the hottest day of the year. 40-degree heat, these boys have to work harder than they ever have. The sun is going to be beating down, they’re going to be sweating, hydration is going to be key today. I also reckon they’re all going to be wearing their sunglasses. Let’s see which shady looking character wins.

programme.title: Strongman Champions League
programme.desc: So there you have it. The next day, 3 more events in 40 Degrees heat. We’ve got Gavin coming into day 2 leading the pack. Kelvin De Ruiter our world champion struggling a little bit at the moment, but Yoke Race, Conan’s Wheel and then Stones to finish. There is a lot to be played for here, so stay tuned to see if Gavin can take the lead and beat Kelvin overall.

programme.title: Strongman Champions League
programme.desc: We’re in the Serbian city of Novi kozarci, for the next stage in the world series. And what a fantastic line up we have for you again. But it is going to be one of the hottest stages yet. A Strongman competition in 44-degree heat. It will be a real challenge for these athletes to finish this event. From all over the world the strongmen came here for the title! Welcome to the heat hell in Serbia.

programme.title: Strongman Champions League
programme.desc: Welcome to day 2 in Serbia, and its another baking hot one. We are in Kikinda today! We’ve got three more gruelling events for our athletes. Sami Ahola is leading the pack, so can he be the first Finnish athlete to take an SCL title. Stay tuned to find out.

programme.title: Strongman Champions League
programme.desc: In this competition, we have our athletes paired up. They’re going to have to take on each event together, having to factor in each other’s strengths and possibly weaknesses. Can the men who normally work alone, share their powers as a duo? Let’s find out!

programme.title: Strongman Champions League
programme.desc: Day 2 of the famous Team World championship here in Finland- Joensuu. Welcome to the final day of the world’s strongest team event. The race to be the best team in the world is coming to its crowing point. All is still wide open for any of these to take the title. Who is going to win? Will team Latvia keep their World Title or maybe Finland can attach them? Keep watching and we’ll find out.

programme.title: Strongman Champions League
programme.desc: Welcome back to Strongman Champions League for another stage of the 2022 world tour. We’re in Esposende - Portugal in this beautiful setting next to the beach in front of a packed crowd with some of the strongest men the world has to offer. With a real Porsche deadlift and many other crazy stuff. So, lets get this show started.

programme.title: Strongman Champions League
programme.desc: Hello and welcome in Gloucester, UK. The world tour hasn’t been here for what feels like forever. And now for the first time in the Mekka of Strongman, the SCL World series will crown a great Champion with the SCL Title. It will be full with special wooden events, and a great winner! So ladies and gentleman, boys and girls, brace yourselves because I present to you strongman champions league UK.

programme.title: Strongman Champions League
programme.desc: We are in Sopot, Poland the home of Legends Mariusz Pudzianowkski and Krzystof Radzikowski. Who will grab the title here in holiday resort Sopot, on the great Balrtic Sea with 6 events and 12 athlets in the mix!

programme.title: Strongman Champions League
programme.desc: We are in Sopot, Poland, after 3 events the Polish Strongman Oskar Ziolkowski is Leading. Kelvin, Travis and Aivars are coming up and will try to beat him, but will Oskar take his first title ever?

programme.title: Strongman Champions League
programme.desc: it’s been a long time since the world series held a championship here in Sarajevo. Let’s see what test of strength this destination holds for our athletes. And what fantastic athletes are here again in Stage 12 of the SCL World Series. The strongman champions league Bosnia is another iconic Strongman event with the return of Rongo Keen from Australia and Portugal winner 2022 George Sulaiman.

programme.title: Strongman Champions League
programme.desc: Welcome to Sibiu in Romania. It’s an important day for some of these athletes, because four of them have a real chance of getting into our all-exclusive world finals. There’s only one more stage after this to get those all-important extra points. So, there’s going to be some fireworks, who will take the title here and who will qualify for the World Finals?

programme.title: Strongman Champions League
programme.desc: This is it the last show before the world final. These guys have really got to fight for the points now, this is going to be action packed, whilst these guys fight it out all day.

programme.title: Strongman Champions League
programme.desc: We are in Alanya, on Turkey’s south-coast for the final stop at the end of a mammoth season of Strongman Champions League. Here in the sunshine, we’ll finally crown our world champion and what a place Alanya is. You could not ask for a better setting. After months of hard-work, if not years for some of these lads, we find out who will take the world title.

programme.title: Strongman Champions League
programme.desc: Welcome, to day two of the strongman champions league 2022 finals here in Alanya, Turkey. It’s all up for grabs now, everyone is fighting for the world title belt. This is an epic episode where we finally crown the World champion of 2022.

The couple secured unprecedented real-time access to the clinical trial in San Diego. What follows is an intimate journey with the patients and scientists who risk everything to be first. In the world of biotech, there are no tidy solutions.

It focuses on autograph dealing, the history of the autograph, autograph conventions, celebrities' point of view, and, of course, the folks whose lives revolve around autographs. Hollywood Signs is a love letter to a world with characters you definitely don't see every day.

programme.title: The Work of Byron Katie
programme.sub-title: My Husband Doesn't Want Me as a Business Partner
programme.desc: Fear is a fickle partner. programme.title: Spiritual Makeover with Marianne Williamson
programme.desc: This is not a religious course; rather, it’s a universal system based on love. You think you have many different problems, but you have only one — the illusion of your separation from God, the true nature of reality. We get trapped in illusions (and create our own suffering) when we over-identify with a particular problem or stay stuck in fear-based thinking. This program is here to remind you of a key universal principle: Only love is real.

programme.title: Bloomberg Daybreak: Australia
programme.desc: Bloomberg continues the expansion of its "Daybreak" franchise with this version that includes reporting from New York and Sydney, Australia. "Daybreak: Australia" delivers news from the Australian market as well as developments from around the world that matter to decision-makers in the finance industry. This installment of "Daybreak" joins other geographically focused versions of the show that highlight financial news in other regions.

programme.title: Bloomberg Daybreak: Asia
programme.desc: With Asia being about half a day ahead of America, when people are getting ready to settle in for the night in the U.S. the day is just starting in places like China and Japan that are important to the global economy. Featuring anchors in both New York and Hong Kong, "Bloomberg Daybreak Asia" features business and financial guests, in addition to providing insights into news and movements in global markets. This installment of "Daybreak" joins other geographically focused versions of the show that highlight financial news in other regions.

programme.title: Bloomberg Markets: China Open
programme.desc: The definitive guide to the markets in Hong Kong and on the mainland; David Ingles and Yvonne Man bring the latest news and analysis to get ready for the trading day.

programme.title: Bloomberg Markets: Asia
programme.desc: In an effort to provide extensive coverage of worldwide financial markets, Bloomberg features several regional shows under the "Bloomberg Markets" banner, with each focusing on that geographic area's markets. This Asian-focused version is hosted by Shery Ahn, David Ingles, Haidi Lun, Rishaad Salamat and Angie Lau. They report the latest business news and speak with the likes of political and business leaders to help investors make investment decisions that build their portfolios.

programme.title: Bloomberg Daybreak: Middle East & Africa
programme.desc: Bringing viewers the latest global markets and analysis, plus news-making interviews, with a special focus on MEA.

programme.title: Bloomberg Daybreak: Middle East & Africa
programme.desc: Bringing viewers the latest global markets and analysis, plus news-making interviews, with a special focus on MEA.

programme.title: Bloomberg Daybreak: Europe
programme.desc: From London, essential morning viewing to stay ahead of the day's market trends with news stories from the U.S. and Asia in the lead-up to the opening of European markets.

programme.title: Bloomberg Markets: Today
programme.desc: Analyzing stories of the day and speaking to guests who have skin in the game as markets open across Europe; hosted by Anna Edwards, Tom Mackenzie and Mark Cudmore.

programme.title: The Pulse with Francine Lacqua
programme.desc: Based in London, Francine Lacqua speaks with high-profile guests in the heart of global business, economics, finance and politics.

programme.title: Bloomberg Brief
programme.desc: "Bloomberg Brief" delivers the market news, data and analysis viewers need to set their agendas.

programme.title: Bloomberg Surveillance
programme.desc: Live from London and New York, with insight on global markets and top business stories of the day.

programme.title: Bloomberg Markets: The Open

programme.title: GLORY Kickboxing
programme.desc: A huge title fight rematch will take place in the main event as rivals Tiffany ‘Time Bomb’ van Soest (24-6-2, 9 KO) and Sarah Moussaddak (8-3, 1 KO) lock horns once again. The rest of the card is stacked with some exciting names and thrilling fights. French Algerian Nordine Mahieddine (27-15, 12 KO) collides with France’s Abderahmane Coulibaly (58-20-1, 25 KO) in a big heavyweight contest, Germany’s Denis Wosik (37-8-1, 9 KO) meets the super popular Albanian Berjan Peposhi (27-3, 16 KO), former GLORY title challenger Karim Ghajji (103-17-1, 53 KO) returns and squares-off against Serbia’s Nikola Todorovic (26-3, 14 KO), and Iliass Hammouche (32-6, 7 KO) will finally make his much anticipated debut against Germany’s Florian Kroger (19-9, 6 KO).

programme.title: GLORY Kickboxing
programme.desc: The undisputed heavyweight king of kickboxing will be decided in the main event as long reigning champion Rico Verhoeven (60-10, 20 KO) goes up against arguably his most dangerous opponent to date in interim-heavyweight champ Tariq ‘Cookie’ Osaro (25-2-1, 13 KO). Middleweight champ Donovan Wisse (19-1, 10 KO) puts his title on the line against number one contender Michael Boapeah (16-3-1, 7 KO). Wisse has looked unstoppable so far during his title run but now he faces an in-form Michael Boapeah who holds a win over the only man to beat Wisse. The welterweight division sees top ranked stars go head-to-head as Hamicha (40-2, 30 KO) takes on Diaguely Camara (24-4-1, 10 KO) and Jay Overmeer (29-5, 15 KO) meets Chico Kwasi (41-5, 22 KO). It’s also an important evening at middleweight with Serkan Ozcaglayan (45-8, 36 KO) colliding with Ulric Bokeme (31-4, 17 KO) and the recently debuted Iliass Hammouche (33-6, 7 KO) facing Ivan Galaz (58-10-1, 15 KO). A huge featherweight match-up between the number one ranked Abraham Vidales (15-2, 12 KO) and number two ranked Ahmad Chikh Mousa (58-8-1, 28 KO) plus an exciting light heavyweight bout between Ibrahim El Bouni (41-8-1, 22 KO) and Stefan Latescu (16-2, 7 KO) will round out the main card.

programme.title: GLORY Kickboxing
programme.desc: The interim-GLORY Heavyweight Title will be up for grabs as top ranked heavyweight contender Antonio Plazibat (22-4, 16 KO) collides with the number two ranked Tariq ‘Cookie’ Osaro (24-2-1, 12 KO) in the main event. These teammates will have to put their friendship aside for one night and go head-to-head for GLORY gold. Also on the card are title fights in the Middleweight, Welterweight and Light Heavyweight divisions.

programme.title: Masters of the Zodiac
programme.desc: Luna-Loo and Tiki have a fight when they are playing with building blocks. They both storm off. Bramble tries to help them make peace with each other, and asks Miss Olivia for help. She prepares a special extracurricular activity for Tiki and Luna-Loo. They have to cooperate with each other to overcome obstacles and win the prize. When they finally get the prize, they realize the importance of teamwork.

programme.title: Masters of the Zodiac
programme.sub-title: A Father’s Love & See the Signs
programme.desc: Babu is unhappy because his father doesn’t compliment him at Parents Day like the other parents. He thinks Barbara is very considerate when he’s learning paper cut in the bears’ house. Babu get blisters from the pair of scissors that is too big for his hand. When he gets home, he’s disappointed to find out his father doesn’t say much about his hand. He goes to take a nap while his father leaves home for work. When his friends come over to his home, however, they find out Babu’s dad have made many thoughtful gadgets for him. He even leaves a special pair of scissors especially made for Babu. Babu realizes that his father loves him in his own way.

programme.title: Masters of the Zodiac
programme.desc: Luna-Loo’s mom is going out for a trip. Her dad grows some flowers, intending to give her mom a surprise when she comes back. Luna-Loo wants to grow some flowers for her mom too, and gets a small lily from her father. She sees some wild flowers can grow very well without anyone tending them, so she decides not to take care of the orchid. The flower looks withered after just a few days. Luna-Loo realizes she needs to put in effort to gain something. She starts to take good care of the lily, which begins to grow well. At last she’s able to present her beautiful flowers to her mom when she comes back.

programme.title: Masters of the Zodiac
programme.sub-title: Ernie Jo’s Gifts & The Paper Boats
programme.desc: Ernie Jo makes a wooden vase, but only Tiki likes it. Ernie Jo is glad Tiki likes weird things just like him. So Ernie Jo gives Tiki a lot of gifts. However, Tiki doesn’t have enough room for those gifts, so he exchanges those gifts for bananas with his friends. Ernie Jo is very angry when he finds out what happens. Tiki realizes his mistake and exchange his gifts back. Ernie Jo the trouble he causes and forgives him. The cubs finally decide to share their gifts with one another.

programme.title: Origins Of The Twelve
programme.desc: The two watchmen land on earth and read out the royal edict to the Kitchen God. The Kitchen God takes over the edict with reverence and awe and follows them onto a mass of cloud heading for the Heaven. They look down at the village on the way and find the masses offering sacrifice to the Kitchen God, praying for happiness and good fortune.

programme.title: Origins Of The Twelve
programme.desc: After travelling miles of the sacred Heaven, the Kitchen God comes to the magnificent Hall of Miraculous Mist in the Golden-gated Cloud Palace. He poses a “V” (stands for victory) gesture with Aquila in front of the palace and asks Sonar to draw a portrait of them to mark the occasion. Shortly after, a lowly clerk comes over and brings the Kitchen God into the palace.

programme.title: Origins Of The Twelve
programme.desc: The Jade Emperor orders Aquila and Sonar to come down to earth and assist the Kitchen God with the task. Meanwhile, Rascal the rat finds the royal edict in the Kitchen God’s house and considers it a good opportunity to change the destinies of his family and himself. Rascal hides the edict to keep other animals from seeing it while the Kitchen God sees through his ruse and tries to recapture the edict. They get into an argument and start to scramble for the edict. Just then, Aquila and Sonar break into the house and join the scramble for the royal edict immediately. In the midst of chaos, the royal edict drops into a censer and is burned into ashes.

programme.title: Origins Of The Twelve
programme.desc: The Kitchen God, Rascal, and the two watchmen stand helplessly in front of the censer. Suddenly, a beam of golden light comes from the hearth and the royal edict floats up to the sky. The edict is made public and the news about the upcoming guardian tournament spreads like wildfire. The Kitchen God feels very remorseful for not keeping the secret. However, Aquila says that in that case they don’t need to worry about where to look for the competitors because all the masters will gather at Mount Tai from every corner of the village at that time.

programme.title: Pondemonium
programme.desc: Joe Croaker is taking a stroll around the Marsh when all of a sudden a giant “owl” falls from the sky. Fearing that the scary bird would devour him, Joe hides himself behind a big rock. Bartle Bee passes by and finds something wrong about this furious “owl”. After a close examination, he discovers that this is not a bird but a paper kite. To fly the kite, Joe slides down a slope to help the kite gain altitude. The kite soars into the sky, taking Joe along on an exciting flight. At first, the fact that he’s ten feet off the ground frightens Joe Croaker. But as he manages to keep the kite under control, he finds himself fascinated by the midair adventure. Joe flies his “glider” and snatches the cheese from Cosmo, which makes the latter really angry. Joe gets completely carried away, when the kite flies into a desert scattered with cacti and becomes out of hand. In the end, Joe crashes in a huge cactus with his “glider”.

programme.title: Pondemonium
programme.desc: Joe Croaker is casting about desperately for something to fill his empty stomach. Luckily for him, he finds some biscuits in a large can. So he jumps right into the can and gobbles up all the biscuits. But after the feast, the frog finds himself unable to get out of the can with an overstuffed belly. He tries all sorts of avenues and finally manages to hop up to the top. Suddenly, the can starts to roll down a slope. Joe freaks out inside the running can and cries for help, which is heard by Cosmo and Bartle Bee who happen to play nearby. They attempt to put a stop to the crazy can, but to no avail. At last, the can is halted on the edge of a cliff. Just when the Bartle Bee and his friends think they are safe, a rock comes running down, knocking the can down into the river. Fortunately enough, the three of them are saved by a large lotus leaf.

programme.title: Pondemonium
programme.desc: Bartle Bee finds a flowering plant in the forest. It is so good-looking that when Bartle Bee leaves, Joe Croaker brings it home and plants it in his back yard. The frog loves the plant and does not allow anyone except himself to touch it. But Cosmo still gets a nimble off one flower petal and the fly becomes extremely aggressive. Cosmo beats Joe Croaker up and makes the frog do his chores and give him massage.

programme.title: Pondemonium
programme.desc: Cosmo finds a discarded solar-powered toy car in the bush. He decides to keep it as a desirable toy. He shows off his new acquisition to Joe Croaker, who is immediately taken with the car as well. Joe Croaker seizes the car from Cosmo and tries to tug it home. As noon comes, the solar-powered car harnesses enough energy from the sun and starts to run on its own. Joe Croaker ties the car to a little tree, trying to keep it still. But fully charged with solar energy, the car breaks free of the restraint and takes Joe Croaker on an exciting road trip. Though a bit scared, Joe gets off on this wild car adventure. He snatches Cosmo’s cheese on the way. The car runs wild again and plunges into a pond, drowning Joe Croaker as well. Cosmo catches up, only to find his cheese cake gone under water.

programme.title: Pondemonium
programme.desc: Cosmo spots a paper boat on the stream. He picks two fine leaves as paddles and begins to go around in his boat. Flutterby is interested in the boat and she asks if she can join Cosmo. Cosmo refuses and Flutterby decides to make one boat on her own. She selects a large leaf and bends it into a boat.

programme.title: Masters of the Zodiac
programme.desc: Briar and Tiki chases their kite to Old Billy’s vegetable patch, and accidentally trample the vegetables. Although they try to correct the deed, but it just get worse. They try to avoid Old Billy in school and hesitate to apologize to him, for fear Old Billy will be angry. Briar tries to get Tiki and apologize to Old Billy. The old man tells them he’s going to the vegetable field to grow new vegetables. Briar and Tiki help him out. At last, they tell Old Billy the truth. The old man doesn’t get angry. Instead, he thinks they are responsible kids.

programme.title: Masters of the Zodiac
programme.desc: Luna-Loo doesn’t want to keep her old or broken toys, and asks her parents to buy her new ones. So she secretly throws away her old toys. When she visits Violet’s home, however, she finds out her friends treasure her toys very much, and remembers the good times she has spent with her toys. Then it rains. Luna-Loo quickly goes outside to find her toys with Violet but can’t find them. She’s feels regret. The next morning, she’s surprised to find out that all her toys are back. It turns out her mom picks up those toys, cleans and mends them. Luna-Loo realizes her mistake and thanks her mom. Violet and Vick come to Luna-Loo’s home and help her modify some old toys. Everyone is happy.

programme.title: Masters of the Zodiac
programme.sub-title: Summoning the Sun & The Frog Friends
programme.desc: Luna-Loo stays at Violet’s home for the night. They borrow a toy car from Vick powered by solar energy. However, the car runs out of power at night. They are disappointed to find out the sun has already set. They decide to summon the sun. First they to use some “magic spells”, then an ice cream to “entice” the sun to come out. They even mimic the sound of roosters to try to call for the sun. The sun never comes out. Instead, Violet’s parents are woken by the noise. Through a little experiment, they explain to the kids about solar rotation and the switch of night and day.

programme.title: Masters of the Zodiac
programme.desc: Briar and Bramble discover that Old Billy’s office smells bad. They decide to help him get rid of the awful smell. They try to collect some fresh clean air from a flower field with bottles, and bring the air to the office. However, it’s hard to tell whether the fragrance is really inside the bottles. So they decide to use balloons to collect the scent. However, a little hedgehog accidentally pops the balloons when he tries to help them. Old Billy sees them and tells them that the stinky smell will go away if they keep good ventilation in the office.

programme.title: Pondemonium
programme.desc: Joe Croaker is frightened upon spying what he believes to be a monster strolling around the pond. He soon realizes that the “monster” is actually a duck, but can’t work out that it’s in fact a toy duck. Assuming that this Rubber Ducky of Death is scheming to occupy his place, Joe Croaker flips out and decides to teach it a good lesson. He bullies the Rubber Ducky of Death until Bartle Bee sweeps it away. Bartle Bee is determined to rescue what he too, sadly, sees as a real—if unresponsive—duck. Joe gives chase to the two runaways, and they tangle with each other. During the confrontation, Bartle Bee accidentally gives the air-filled toy duck a prick with his sting, causing it to deflate and fly away. Still in the dark, Bartle Bee blames the disappearance of the poor little “creature” on Joe Croaker.

programme.title: Pondemonium
programme.desc: Joe Croaker finds a balloon dinosaur among the grass. The frog has no idea what he has discovered and he really panics at this “dinosaur” that is many times his own size. Joe Croaker begins to attack the balloon with pebbles he picks up from the ground. One of the pebbles bounces off the balloon and hits Bartle Bee’s honey jar on the ground. Though Joe Croaker tells Bartle Bee that he has nothing to do with the broken honey jar, the bee is smart enough to figure it out by himself.

programme.title: Pondemonium
programme.desc: Cosmo eats up all the food Joe Croaker has obtained, which puts the latter into a violate passion. And his mockery about Joe Croaker’s inability to fly adds fuel to fire. The hot-air balloons floating in the sky inspire the frog, who then manages to put together one with all the parts he collects from the garbage can. Flying with the ill-made balloon, Joe Croaker grabs the food from Cosmo and endeavors to catch the fly. But the balloon is too slow for Cosmo, so Joe plays dead to bamboozle Cosmo, who falls for it and ends up being caught. Just at that moment, the candle in the balloon exhausts itself. Both Joe Croaker and Cosmo fall to the ground, where the frog resumes his chase after his little foe.

programme.title: Pondemonium
programme.desc: Joe Croaker comes across a roly-poly toy when he is trying to get some candy near a dumpster. It’s a big smiling face doll. But the frog has no knowledge of what he is facing. He sees the roly-poly as a potential threat to him and the Marsh. Joe Croaker challenges the toy and attempts to take it down. The frog fails and finally he uses a rope to tie the roly-poly toy up.

programme.title: Pondemonium
programme.desc: As the dung balls keep piling up, McBroom finds himself short of energy to get his work done all by himself. At Bartle Bee’s suggestion, he puts up a recruitment ad to look for someone to help him. The handsome benefits offered on this job allure many insects over, including Hercules Beetle, Snout Beetle and Bartle Bee. To select the best out of the three candidates, McBroom put them on a series of tests where Hercules Beetle stands out to win the position as McBroom’s assistant. Much to McBroom’s disappointment, however, his employee turns out to be quite lazy. So he has to give Hercules Beetle the sack and send him home.

programme.title: Origins Of The Twelve
programme.desc: Hammer the ox is an excellent blacksmith in his village but he only makes weapons. The village head persuades him to sell them at Carrotown because the market there is much larger. Hammer follows his advice and heads for Carrotown. Along the road, the ox tries to promote his weapons to an lumberjack and a watermelon farmer but they all mistake him for a robber and are scared to death.

programme.title: Origins Of The Twelve
programme.desc: Velvet Touch and Trapper are walking through the forest. Unexpectedly, two hedgehogs stand in their way and plan to plunder their valuables. Velvet Touch throws two darts to them, which annoys the two robbers. They contract their bodies into two spiky balls and roll toward her. To protect Velvet Touch, Trapper rushes over and hits them with a long stick. He puts on an awesome Kung Fu show and transforms into Mad Wolf. After Trapper realizes he has spilt the beans, he deliberately loses out to hedgehogs and surrenders to them.

programme.title: Origins Of The Twelve
programme.desc: At night, three animals make a campfire and sit down for a rest. Velvet Touch keeps commending Hammer upon his braveness and complains about Trapper’s cowardice. Velvet Touch thinks Hammer can serve as a good bodyguard and persuades him to go with them together the next day. Hammer accepts her invitation with alacrity. The next morning, they continue on their way. The rabbit suggests to perform juggling acts to attract villagers over and sell Hammer’s weapons to them. Others nod their appreciation.

programme.title: Origins Of The Twelve
programme.desc: Artisan, the richest rooster in the world, writes a piece of calligraphy. All the officials curry favor with Artisan and praise him for creating such a masterpiece. However, the truth is that Artisan is an illiterate and the so-called calligraphy is just his scrawled handwritings. Artisan strolls to the backyard of his palace and sees a kite flying in the sky. On a whim, he decides to make a peerless kite by himself. He orders his attendant to choose the most expensive materials.

programme.title: Masters of the Zodiac
programme.sub-title: Tiki’s Dancing Lesson & Mom and Me
programme.desc: Tiki admires Violet’s dancing. The kids all want Violet to teach them how to dance. Tiki goes to Violet’s home the next day. On his way there his friends tell him dancing is very difficult. He tries to learn some moves from Vick but he feel discouraged. He still continues to learn as Violet keeps encouraging him. But due to his nervousness, he steps on Luna-Loo many times while practicing. Luna-Loo tries to help him relax but none of the method works. Tiki dances in his own way and relaxes. He finally learns how to dance. He realizes he can’t just give up when others say it’s difficult.

programme.title: Masters of the Zodiac
programme.sub-title: The Pink Racket & A Promising Flower
programme.desc: The cubs are playing badminton in the kindergarten. Herbert likes the pink racket. However, he overhears the others say the color pink is only for girls. So he does not dare to take the pink one, even though the one he uses is broken during the match. Then Old Billy joins them. The kids laugh at his floral shirt, but Old Billy doesn’t seem to care. Herbert understands he doesn’t need to pay too much attention to others’ opinions, and decides to use the pink racket.

programme.title: Masters of the Zodiac
programme.desc: The cubs are rehearsing a show. At first, Babu acts well in his role. However, he becomes nervous when Warren and Luna-Loo come to watch the rehearsal. He forgets his lines, and can’t act. Babu thinks he didn’t practice enough but Luna-Loo thinks he has stage fright. He gives his role to Ernie Jo. Then Babu’s dad helps him to overcome his stage fright, and asks him to imagine the audience as fruits. At last, Babu doesn’t feel nervous anymore and acts well in the show.

programme.title: Masters of the Zodiac
programme.sub-title: A Party at Violet’s & Got a Spare?
programme.desc: Violet invites her friends to her home, and has made proper arrangement. She thinks things will go smoothly. However, when her friends come to her house, they don’t want to follow her arrangements. They want to eat cakes and play with the ball. Violet doesn’t know what to do. Her father tells her that she should discuss with her friends about what to do. Violet listens to her friends’ opinions, and they all have fun.

programme.title: Pondemonium
programme.desc: Briar has a toothache and Vick tells him there are bugs eating his teeth, making him anxious. To get the bugs out, they try many methods, such as gargling water, asking Hoo Hoo to peck the bugs out, and singing to lure the bugs out, all of which are proven to be useless. At last, they go to see Nurse Beakman, then they find out the cause of tooth decay, and learn how to protect their teeth.

programme.title: Pondemonium
programme.desc: Violet has a treasure chest, inside which Luna-Loo likes the moon stone the most. That day, Luna-Loo hides the treasure chest somewhere else without Violet’s permission, but what she doesn’t know is that Ms. Lady Jane witnesses the whole thing. Tiki goes to find Old Billy and asks him what’s wrong with the weather forecast. Old Billy explains that nature changes constantly and that only by studying hard could they make weather forecasts as accurate as possible.

programme.title: Pondemonium
programme.desc: Joe Croaker picks up a bouncy ball among the grass and takes it home. This small ball bounces around in a way that the frog cannot control. Joe Croaker now is standing on it and the bouncy ball begins to roll down a slope. The frog attempts tries to stop the ball but he simply is not able to mange. It takes the frog some agility and luck to avoid the rocks and tree branches in his way and finally he is stopped by one of McBroom’s dung balls.

programme.title: Pondemonium
programme.desc: Bartle Bee accidentally sets foot in a place studded with numerous full-blown flowers. Overjoyed, he plans to have a good time collecting nectar there. Then there comes a mean bee who tries to beat him up, accusing Bartle of trespassing on his turf. Intimidated, Bartle has to run away from that flourishing land. Flutterby learns of the whole story and decides to help her little buddy punish the bad bee. She paints two horrible huge eyes on the leaves and uses them to scare off the villainous bee. Then Bartle Bee sets up the leaves in the field, but a gust of wind blows them off to the ground, revealing the truth to the vicious bee. In his pursuit of Bartle Bee, the bully bee runs into a big bird which he believes to be a fake one for setting him up. He throws stones at the bird, only to be chased by the furious creature. Just when the bird is about to swallow him, Bartle Bee and Flutterby show up. They distract the bird and save the bee’s life. In the end, the three of them put behind the grudge and become friends.

programme.title: Pondemonium
programme.desc: Joe Croaker comes across a slingshot in the Marsh. He soon realizes that it is a decent swing. The frog then takes a thorough examination of the slingshot. He is convinced that he can shoot some pebbles with this new toy he just found. The pebbles cause damage to the neighboring insects and Joe Croaker could not stop there. He finds a box of pushpins and starts to shoot them.

programme.title: Pondemonium
programme.desc: Cosmo brags about seeing a long train in front of Joe Croaker. The fly can see the world from above in the mid air but Joe Croaker cannot. This upsets the frog. Joe Croaker figures that if he climbs up to the top of the tree, he will be able to get a better view there. But sadly for Joe Croaker, on a long list of the things he can achieve, climbing isn’t one of them. Advised by Cosmo, Joe Croaker makes many failed attempts to climb up the tree. First he tries to do it by sticking the double-sided tape to his limbs, which results in a heavy fall from the tree. Then Cosmo fetches him a rope with a big hook that is intended to be attached to the tree and help Joe up. But it falls and almost has Cosmo crushed. In the end, on Bartle’s suggestion, Cosmo helps Joe Croaker build up a firm ladder which Joe Croaker takes to reach the top of the tree. But when up there, Joe realizes that he is afraid of heights!

Hammer follows his advice and heads for Carrotown. Along the road, the ox tries to promote his weapons to an lumberjack and a watermelon farmer but they all mistake him for a robber and are scared to death.

programme.title: Origins Of The Twelve
programme.desc: Velvet Touch and Trapper are walking through the forest. Unexpectedly, two hedgehogs stand in their way and plan to plunder their valuables. Velvet Touch throws two darts to them, which annoys the two robbers. They contract their bodies into two spiky balls and roll toward her. To protect Velvet Touch, Trapper rushes over and hits them with a long stick. He puts on an awesome Kung Fu show and transforms into Mad Wolf. After Trapper realizes he has spilt the beans, he deliberately loses out to hedgehogs and surrenders to them.

programme.title: Origins Of The Twelve
programme.desc: At night, three animals make a campfire and sit down for a rest. Velvet Touch keeps commending Hammer upon his braveness and complains about Trapper’s cowardice. Velvet Touch thinks Hammer can serve as a good bodyguard and persuades him to go with them together the next day. Hammer accepts her invitation with alacrity. The next morning, they continue on their way. The rabbit suggests to perform juggling acts to attract villagers over and sell Hammer’s weapons to them. Others nod their appreciation.

programme.title: Origins Of The Twelve
programme.desc: Artisan, the richest rooster in the world, writes a piece of calligraphy. All the officials curry favor with Artisan and praise him for creating such a masterpiece. However, the truth is that Artisan is an illiterate and the so-called calligraphy is just his scrawled handwritings. Artisan strolls to the backyard of his palace and sees a kite flying in the sky. On a whim, he decides to make a peerless kite by himself. He orders his attendant to choose the most expensive materials.

programme.title: Masters of the Zodiac
programme.sub-title: Tiki’s Dancing Lesson & Mom and Me
programme.desc: Tiki admires Violet’s dancing. The kids all want Violet to teach them how to dance. Tiki goes to Violet’s home the next day. On his way there his friends tell him dancing is very difficult. He tries to learn some moves from Vick but he feel discouraged. He still continues to learn as Violet keeps encouraging him. But due to his nervousness, he steps on Luna-Loo many times while practicing. Luna-Loo tries to help him relax but none of the method works. Tiki dances in his own way and relaxes. He finally learns how to dance. He realizes he can’t just give up when others say it’s difficult.

programme.title: Stacey David's Gearz
programme.desc: Season 10 Starts off with America’s favorite military tribute truck! Sgt. Rock is back and ready for final assembly! Garage Guru, Stacey David, takes us on a tour de force of custom fabrication as he covers all the nuts and bolts of what it’s taken to get Sgt. Rock ready to rumble. Builders of all levels are in for a great show as Stacey tackles one of a kind steering columns, gas pedals and designing a console that not only fits form, but also function. Gauge techs will keep your instrument panels in line. And a quick tip will keep your wires from fraying and your hoses from splitting. All this and more as Sgt. Rock and Season 10 hit the road full throttle.

programme.title: Stacey David's Gearz
programme.desc: A custom build can lose some power if the theme doesn’t stay consistent. Stacey shows how to do that by taking you through the process of how to make door and kick panels that keep the rugged military WWII bomber vibe flowing throughout the interior of Sgt. Rock. After that, its some tips on how to fit a radiator and that all-important cooling fan in a place where space is limited. Finally, the gas tank and battery placement are critical on a custom vehicle and Stacey goes through the steps in doing that as well. If you’ve always wanted to build a custom vehicle, this episode is sure to get your fabrication gearZ turning.

programme.title: AmeriCarna
programme.desc: The last car Elvis drove the evening he passed was his beloved Stutz Blackhawk. Ray discovers that the car has been preserved and heads to Graceland to check out this iconic piece of American music history. Ray and the team reveal the impeccable preservation of the car at Charlotte Motor Speedway with Rick Hendrick (“Mr. H”) and, arguably Elvis Presley’s biggest fan, Dale Earnhardt Jr. While at Graceland, Ray and the team also get an exclusive look at the paneled station wagon Elvis used to get in and out of Graceland in disguise. It’s an intimate look at the King’s incredible automobiles and their secrets that only Elvis knew.

programme.title: AmeriCarna
programme.desc: This episode takes an inside look at the famous racing L88 Corvette. From its history, to its successes and heartbreaks, to the stories of the men that drove it. Now, it’s a car world’s version of the Flinstones meet the Jetsons, as the Owens Corning Corvette, which clinched 22 straight race victories, challenges the new Corvette C7-R at Sebring International Raceway. The original Owens Corning team reunites for the challenge and our crew goes behind the scenes for the Corvette test drive of a lifetime.

programme.title: AmeriCarna
programme.desc: From break up to make up, Jeff Gordon and Ray reunite to go on a quest to find their Chevrolet Monte Carlo that claimed victory in their final race together at Phoenix, AZ in 1999. John Bickford, Jeff Gordon’s stepdad, makes the call that reunites the old team. Jeff and Ray look to bum parts off their boss, Rick Hendrick, to make their vision a reality: get the car, replace the parts as they were, make it run and get it to auction.

programme.title: AmeriCarna
programme.desc: One of the greatest battles in NASCAR history was Hall of Famer Richie Evans and rival speedster Jerry Cook. Ray is determined to uncover and revive the cars that made these men famous.Ray purchases one of Richie’s original #61 modifieds from Jimmy Spencer and restores it to its original glory while simultaneously building a replica of Jerry Cook’s #38. Throughout the build process, Ray uncovers stories about these legends through the eyes of guys who were in Rome, NY to witness it firsthand, like Robin Pemberton and Steve Hmiel.Both cars will hit the track at Martinsville, site of one of the greatest races in modified history and the tragic death of Richie Evans himself. Legends live again, as Ray recreates one of the racing world’s most celebrated rivalries on a track that has seen it all.

programme.title: AmeriCarna
programme.desc: General Motors VP of global design Ed Welburn takes AmeriCarna behind the scenes to talk about the history and development of the company’s concept cars that never made it to production. In a rare tour of the factory’s inner design studio, Ray gets an exclusive look behind the creative curtain at the GM plant in Detroit.

programme.title: AmeriCarna
programme.desc: In this episode, Ray celebrates the 50th birthday of the Ford Mustang through the lens of three distinct Mustang owners, who each hold a slice of the car’s incredible history. In 1964, Chicago schoolteacher Gail Wise unknowingly purchased the first ever Mustang 3 days before the car became available to the general public. Her husband reveals the incredible restoration that brought the earliest Mustang ever sold back to its 60’s glory. (Ford Motor Company knows she has the car and has verified it was sold before it was legal to sell.) John Grafelman is a farmer in Illinois and life-long Ford lover. A few years ago he found an old car hidden in a barn. It took some time, but he eventually convinced his friend to sell it to him. After some detective work, he discovers he purchased 1968 Ford Design Chief Larry Shinoda’s personal car that he tinkered with to invent the BOSS 302.Lastly, Ray travels to Dayton Ohio to interview Gale Holderman, the Ford stylist who won the company’s contest to draw and design the Mustang.

programme.title: AmeriCarna
programme.desc: A massive sinkhole opened underneath the National Corvette Museum in Kentucky. Eight amazing cars were swallowed up, including the 1,000,000th Corvette. AmeriCarna was given exclusive access to document the removal of the cars from the sinkhole and the painstaking restoration of the 1,000,000th Corvette.

But the next morning there is no present under the pillow. The Mouse Fairy has not been. She has been captured in one of Gargamel’s Smurf traps. And now the evil wizard is concocting a dreadful plan.

programme.title: The Smurfs
programme.desc: We all know Grouchy Smurf hates a lot of things. But one thing he hates more than anything else is water, when there is enough of it to drown in. You see, Grouchy can't swim. And when the Smurfs notice this peculiarity and try to teach him how to survive in water, the evil wizard Gargamel makes things a little more dangerous than they ought to be....

programme.title: The Smurfs
programme.desc: Gargamel infects Hefty's heart with hate and then uses the little Smurf as a decoy for the others. Fortunately, Hefty's love overcomes his hate and he helps his little friends escape from Gargamel's clutches.

programme.title: Alarming Smurfs
programme.desc: Feeling unwanted, the Smurflings run away. They take things to remind them of home, so the Smurfs think there's a thief in their midst. Brainy tries to catch the thief by installing smurfler alarms. The alarms cause a ruckus that draws the Smurflings home, where Papa tells them they are wanted.

programme.title: The Smurfs
programme.desc: In old Mesopotamia, after Smurfette pricks her thumb on the thorn of a magic flower, anything she touches turns into a plant. Can Papa save her from the evil flowers of Babble-on?

programme.title: The Smurfs
programme.desc: Being Papa Smurf has its share of joys but also a few disadvantages. Such as being interrupted every five minutes, even when in the middle of delicate magic experiments. So Papa wonders if it's not possible to be replaced by a decision-taking Smurf...

programme.title: The Horn Of Plenty
programme.desc: Mother Nature always does her best, but this time she's gone wrong. Her wand gets the wrong results and she accidentally damages the Autumn harvest. Now the Smurfs and all the forest animals face a lean and hungry winter. The only place where the Smurfs could get food would be the Land of Plenty. But Gargamel steals the famed Horn of Plenty to lure the Smurfs.

programme.title: The Smurfs
programme.desc: This is the dramatic, moving story of the friendship between Smurfette and her pet mouse. A sad event reduces Smurfette to tears... Can the Smurfs comfort the despairing Smurfette?

programme.title: The Smurfs
programme.desc: Smurfette leads the Smurflings on a nature hike, but Puppy gets too far ahead and they chase him into the land of the Wartmongers. King Bullrush captures them in bubbles and imprisons them. A group of rebels rescue the Smurflings and they escape on the back of Puppy.

programme.title: The Smurfs
programme.desc: Gargamel's theft of the Fairies' gold almost brings a state of war between the Fairies and the Smurfs.

programme.title: The Smurfs
programme.desc: The wizard Gargamel creates an enticing Smurfette to lure the Smurfs into his castle. The Smurfette is thoroughly entranced with the little Smurfs, becomes one of them and together they cause Gargamel's wicked plan to backfire on him. With a magic spell Papa Smurf finally succeeds in making Smurfette look more Smurflike. It is no longer possible for Gargamel to dictate his evil orders through her powder box's mirror.

programme.title: Revenge Of The Smurfs
programme.desc: A war is raging in the Middle Ages. Knights in armor in hot pursuit inadvertently destroy the Smurfs Village so a small band of Smurfs decide to avenge this wrongdoing. Won't Papa Smurf think this is too human-like a reaction?

programme.title: The Smurfs
programme.desc: Handy Smurf has saved Clumsy from a horrible fate. Clumsy swears eternal devotion to his savior and does his best to repay his debt... With awkward results. A clever scheme is needed to stop Clumsy's well-meant catastrophes...

programme.title: The Smurfs
programme.desc: How can the Smurfs save this future baby vulture? Right now, it's still in the egg and they must find a way of incubating the bird. And it just happens that the evil wizard Gargamel has found a way of changing himself into a bird to get at the Smurfs...

programme.title: It Came From Outer Smurf
programme.desc: Dreamy wants to encounter beings from outer space so much that no one believes him when he talks of having met one. Yet the arrival of this extraterrestrial is going to wreak havoc in the Smurf Village...

programme.title: All Creatures Great And Smurf
programme.desc: Nat Smurf is convinced he can help all creatures with his healing ways, even the wicked Azrael after he gets his paw caught in a trap. He heals well, but even though he is tempted to stay with the Smurfs, he runs back to Gargamel while leading his old master away from Smurf Village.

programme.title: The Smurfs
programme.desc: While out on a mischief-making mission to destroy the Smurfs' Happy Halloween party, Gargamel and Hogatha catch Lazy who has been accidentally turned red by Mother Nature. Papa and the Smurfs help Lazy escape while Mother Nature has Father Time help turn Lazy's red into blue just in time for the Halloween party.

programme.title: The Smurfs
programme.desc: Despite Grandpa's warning that it is wrong to take wild animals away from their habitat, the Smurflings, back from a long trip in the magic balloon, bring along a Nebbit, a funny, loveable creature. Funny and loveable for a little while, but then matters get more complex...

programme.title: The Smurfs
programme.desc: The Smurfs arrive in Camelot to witness several events: treacherous Morgan Le Fay steals Excalibur, the magic sword, and turns Merlin the Wizard, King Arthur and Lancelot into helpless victims.

programme.title: The Bad Place
programme.desc: What is this little moon coming from above? Why, it's a crater-pockmarked globe of mud inhabited by the Grimeys, a family of mud-splattering, mud-eating creatures from out there in the sky. Not all the Smurfs are enthusiastic about the visitors....

programme.title: The Smurfs
programme.desc: In the times of Greek antiquity, a spoiled heiress meets Smurfette and believes she's the most beautiful doll she has ever seen. To save Smurfette, Papa Smurf resorts to an old trick...

programme.title: The Smurfs
programme.sub-title: Journey To The Centre Of The Smurf
programme.desc: Winter is setting in on the Village of the Smurfs. The little Smurfs are freezing. But what is Clumsy doing with this strange rock he's discovered? And why is Miner Smurf so enthusiastic about their new discovery? Surely, one more addition to Clumsy's rock collection is not worth all this hoopla... The Smurfs will discover danger and surprises when they go underground.

programme.title: The Smurfs
programme.desc: Handy Smurf has hit on a revolutionary new idea: a sort of smurfless carriage that moves on railroad tracks. He calls it a railsmurfer and it makes for less work in the Village... until Gargamel chances upon it.

programme.title: The Smurfs
programme.desc: The Smurfs arrive in Camelot to witness several events: treacherous Morgan Le Fay steals Excalibur, the magic sword, and turns Merlin the Wizard, King Arthur and Lancelot into helpless victims.

programme.title: The Smurfs
programme.desc: The wizard Gargamel creates an enticing Smurfette to lure the Smurfs into his castle. The Smurfette is thoroughly entranced with the little Smurfs, becomes one of them and together they cause Gargamel's wicked plan to backfire on him. With a magic spell Papa Smurf finally succeeds in making Smurfette look more Smurflike. It is no longer possible for Gargamel to dictate his evil orders through her powder box's mirror.

programme.title: The Smurfs
programme.desc: Handy has built a very complex Smurf machine that does everything. It proves dangerous when it nearly destroys the village, but comes in useful when, with the help of the other Smurfs, it saves the young prince Gerard's kingdom from the queen aunt Imperia's dastardly intentions.

programme.title: The Smurfs
programme.desc: There are few things Grandpa Smurf enjoys more than telling a good scary story, and there are few Smurfs who don't love to listen. But things get a little too much for Brainy Smurf when Grandpa tells of Poltersmurfs, and Poltersmurfs begin harrowing Brainy...

programme.title: The Smurfs
programme.desc: The evil wizard Gargamel wants to create a monster. A horrible, gigantic creature, an awesome being that is going to destroy all the Smurfs! But Gargamel makes a slight mistake, and the result is going to astonish him and his cat Azrael.

programme.title: The Smurfs
programme.desc: It's been a few hundred years since Grandpa Smurf has seen this old toy... It was given to Papa Smurf long, long ago and he does not remember what it does. But Baby Smurf does know that it brings surprises for everyone!

programme.title: The Smurfs
programme.desc: Being Papa Smurf has its share of joys but also a few disadvantages. Such as being interrupted every five minutes, even when in the middle of delicate magic experiments. So Papa wonders if it's not possible to be replaced by a decision-taking Smurf...

programme.title: The Magic Stick
programme.desc: With a borrowed recipe from Homnibus, Papa Smurf creates a magic stick that Clumsy takes and loses in the woods. Soon after, Bigmouth comes for a visit and before he eats all the smurfberries, Papa Smurf finds the magic stick and whisks the giant away.

programme.title: All The News That's Fit To Smurf
programme.desc: Curious Smurf has an idea: why not print a sheet with all the Village news? He's sure to interest all his readers of the Smurf Tattler. But things don't go exactly to plan when Papa finds super smurfberries.

programme.title: The Smurfs
programme.desc: Hogatha, the repulsive witch, captures the Smurfette. She wants to steal from the little blue beauty her golden hair. Can the Smurfs save their little female companion before it is too late? Can Hogatha grow hair like Smurfette's?

programme.title: Brainy Smurf, Friend To All Animals
programme.desc: Brainy dons his safari hat and roams the forest to do good deeds for animals. He mostly gives advice to the creatures but balks when he can really save the life of a wildcat being hunted by Gargamel. Nat gives Brainy the courage to free the cat from Gargamel's trap.

programme.title: The Smurfs
programme.desc: In Egypt there is a cat pharaoh called Azrael and the name rings a bell with the Smurfs. As does the cruel taskmaster's name! Gargahotep wants to enslave the Smurfs to build a pyramid...

programme.title: The Smurfs
programme.desc: Dreamy's wish of becoming an Astrosmurf comes true when Papa Smurf puts him to sleep, magically transforming the landscape and the Smurfs into a space fantasy. Gargamel keeps a close watch on their antics through his crystal ball, but he too falls victim to Papa Smurf's magic and is sent into a thunderstorm.

programme.title: The Smurfs
programme.desc: Clumsy Smurf's misadventures take him across a river into Pussywillow Hollow. There he meets the Pixies – charming and shapely beings whose enemies, the Wartmongers, will meet the Smurfs in some unforeseen ways.

programme.title: The Smurfs
programme.desc: Brainy Smurf's done it again. This time, in front of Papa Smurf, too. He has recited a spell that changes everything to stone. Everything including himself and all the Smurfs and the Village, and the forest around for miles... Fortunately, Peewit appears....

programme.title: The Smurfs
programme.desc: The village of the Smurfs used to live without a clock. But now suddenly time becomes a precious commodity and Brainy Smurf designs a schedule to take advantage of the new Village clock... Can the Smurfs survive the attacks of time?

programme.title: Vanity Fair
programme.desc: Gargamel's magic mirror traps Vanity Smurf inside it so Smurfette and Brainy rush to his rescue. Once inside the mirror-world, they cause a giant explosion that shatters the glassy enclosure and hurry back to their smurfy village.
